{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: research-study-and-subject_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates TWO FSH instances in a single template pass:

      1. ResearchStudy  — a largely static description of the EU BEUDIS
                          clinical trial (fictitious study used for synthetic
                          data generation).
      2. ResearchSubject — links the patient being processed to the above
                           study, with their ECI as the participant identifier.

    This template is used to attach IPS/EPS Research Study information to a
    patient record when the patient is enrolled in a study. Both instances are
    emitted contiguously in the %%FSH%% section and registered separately via
    two `setInstance()` calls.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    ResearchStudy  : base FHIR R4 ResearchStudy resource (no additional profile)
    ResearchSubject: base FHIR R4 ResearchSubject resource (no additional profile)

  TWO-INSTANCE PATTERN
    This template calls `setInstance()` twice. Both returned names are collected
    into the `twigit()` return array in call order:
      index 0 → "Instance-ResearchStudy-<researchstudyinstanceid>"
      index 1 → "Instance-ResearchSubject-<researchsubjectinstanceid>"
    The ResearchSubject references the ResearchStudy by a `urn:uuid:` reference
    constructed from `researchstudyinstanceid`.

  STATIC VS DYNAMIC CONTENT
    The ResearchStudy body is intentionally largely hardcoded — it describes
    a single fictitious study ("BEUDIS") used across all synthetic patients.
    Only the instance id (`researchstudyinstanceid`) is dynamic.
    The ResearchSubject body is dynamic: the patient's ECI is embedded and the
    study reference is constructed from the study instance id.

  HTML NARRATIVE PATTERN  ← differs from other templates
    The HTML bag and HEAD bag are built inside the ResearchStudy block (before
    it ends) but are emitted inside the ResearchSubject's `text.div`. This
    means BOTH bags are flushed together in the second instance's narrative,
    producing a single combined table that covers both resources.

    In `text.div` of ResearchSubject:
      {{ emitHEAD() | raw }} {{ emitHTML() | raw }}
    Note: `emitHEAD()` is called here (not only in %%HEAD%%) so the narrative
    table includes the column headers inline.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                   │ Type     │ Description                        │
  ├────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ researchstudyinstanceid    │ string   │ Unique id for the ResearchStudy    │
  │                            │          │ resource. Used to compose the FSH  │
  │                            │          │ instance name and the urn:uuid:    │
  │                            │          │ reference in ResearchSubject.      │
  │ researchsubjectinstanceid  │ string   │ Unique id for the ResearchSubject  │
  │                            │          │ resource.                          │
  │ patient.eci                │ string   │ European Citizen Identifier of the │
  │                            │          │ patient, used as the participant   │
  │                            │          │ identifier (type PT, system ECI).  │
  └────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $sct       — SNOMED CT; condition code 44054006 "Diabetes mellitus type 2"
    $v2-0203   — HL7 v2 Table 0203 identifier type; PT = Patient (participant)
    (ISO 3166-1 RegionCode #EUR is used directly as a FHIR code for `location`)

  STATIC STUDY DATA (hardcoded for the BEUDIS fictitious study)
    Identifier : FBEUDIS7395z67927  (system: https://clinicaltrials.eu)
    Title      : "The Big EU Diabetis Study (BEUDIS) Phase 4"
    Purpose    : #treatment
    Phase      : #phase-4
    Condition  : SCT#44054006  Diabetes mellitus type 2
    Status     : #active
    Location   : #EUR

  STATIC SUBJECT DATA (hardcoded UUID for participant slot)
    Identifier : 40f978c4-0d32-422e-bc07-5f99db9c27c7
                 (secondary, system: https://beudis.eu)
    Status     : #candidate

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2026-02-26
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

{#
  ── ResearchStudy instance ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Emitted first. The body is intentionally static — all synthetic patients
  reference the same BEUDIS study description.
  Only the instance id is dynamic (injected via researchstudyinstanceid).
#}
Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-ResearchStudy-" ~ researchstudyinstanceid) }}
InstanceOf: ResearchStudy
Title: "ResearchStudy"
Description: "ResearchStudy Information"
Usage: #inline

{#
  ── HEAD bag: table column headers ─────────────────────────────────────────
  Two columns: study title and status. Emitted here so they sit logically
  alongside the study block, even though they are flushed in the
  ResearchSubject's text.div and in %%HEAD%% below.
#}
{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Participant in Study") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Status") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

* id = "{{ researchstudyinstanceid }}"

{#
  ── Business identifier ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Official trial registration number on https://clinicaltrials.eu.
  This is static for the BEUDIS study.
#}
* identifier[+].use    = #official
* identifier[=].system = "https://clinicaltrials.eu"
* identifier[=].value  = "FBEUDIS7395z67927"

{#
  ── Study metadata (all static for BEUDIS) ──────────────────────────────────
  The multi-line `description` uses FSH's triple-quote syntax and includes
  Markdown bold formatting, which is valid within FSH string values.
#}
* title              = "The Big EU Diabetis Study (BEUDIS) Phase 4"
* description        = """
This fictous study aims on treating **Diabetis Type 2** patients in the European Union with a brand new drug called "Combattente"
"""
* primaryPurposeType = #treatment
* phase              = #phase-4

* condition = $sct#44054006 "Diabetes mellitus type 2 (disorder)"

* status   = #active

{#
  ── Location: EU region ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ISO 3166-1 region code #EUR flags this as a European-region study.
#}
* location = #EUR

{#
  ── ResearchStudy narrative ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  A placeholder narrative ("tbd") is used here because the study description
  is static and its full human-readable form is deferred. The ResearchSubject
  carries the combined HTML table narrative for both instances.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
tbd
</div>
"""

{#
  ── ResearchSubject instance ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Emitted second, in the same %%FSH%% section. Links the patient to the study
  above via a urn:uuid: Reference. The patient is identified by their ECI.
#}
Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-ResearchSubject-" ~ researchsubjectinstanceid) }}
InstanceOf: ResearchSubject
Title: "ResearchSubject"
Description: "ResearchSubject Information"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ researchsubjectinstanceid }}"

{#
  ── Secondary participant identifier ───────────────────────────────────────
  A study-internal UUID assigned to the participant slot within BEUDIS.
  Typed #secondary as it is a local study number rather than a national id.
#}
* identifier[+].use    = #secondary
* identifier[=].system = "https://beudis.eu"
* identifier[=].value  = "40f978c4-0d32-422e-bc07-5f99db9c27c7"

* status = #candidate

{#
  ── Back-reference to the ResearchStudy ────────────────────────────────────
  Uses the same researchstudyinstanceid that was set in the Instance above,
  constructing a urn:uuid: reference to link subject → study within the Bundle.
#}
* study = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ researchstudyinstanceid }})

{#
  ── Patient identifier on the subject record ───────────────────────────────
  Two individual[] slices: the identifier type (PT = Patient) and the ECI.
  Note: [+] is used for both the type slice and the system/value pair, each
  as separate slices of `individual`. This establishes the patient's ECI as
  the participant identifier in the study.
#}
* individual[+].type   = $v2-0203#PT
* individual[+].use    = #official
* individual[=].system = "http://ec.europa.eu/identifier/eci"
* individual[=].value  = "{{ patient.eci }}"

{#
  ── Combined HTML narrative ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Unusually, both emitHEAD() and emitHTML() are flushed inside this second
  instance's text.div — not the first. This produces a single table in the
  ResearchSubject narrative that covers the study participation information.
  The hl7__ips first25 CSS classes are applied: first25 constrains the width
  of the first column to 25% in the vi7eti stylesheet.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips first25">{{ emitHEAD() | raw }} {{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
